PortList.name: PortList
PortList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

VlanIndex.name: VlanIndex
VlanIndex.description: A value used to index per-VLAN tables: values of 0 and 4095 are not permitted; if the value is between 1 and 4094 inclusive, it represents an IEEE 802.1Q VLAN-ID with global scope within a given bridged domain (see VlanId textual convention). If the value is greater than 4095 then it represents a VLAN with scope local to the particular agent, i.e. one without a global VLAN-ID assigned to it. Such VLANs are outside the scope of IEEE 802.1Q but it is convenient to be able to manage them in the same way using this MIB.

InterfaceIndex.name: InterfaceIndex
InterfaceIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface or interface sub-layer in the managed system. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

DropDirection.name: DropDirection
DropDirection.description: Representing the direction of dropping packets, if applicable.

hwifXXTable.name: hwifXXTable
hwifXXTable.description: Extended Huawei private interface information table.

hwifXXEntry.name: hwifXXEntry
hwifXXEntry.description: Entries of extended Huawei private interface information table.

hwifUnBoundPort.name: hwifUnBoundPort
hwifUnBoundPort.description: Whether it is the unbound port. (true indicates that the port is the main port of the aggregation or the port does not participate in the aggregation.)

hwifISPhyPort.name: hwifISPhyPort
hwifISPhyPort.description: Whether it is a physical interface.

hwifAggregatePort.name: hwifAggregatePort
hwifAggregatePort.description: Whether it is the aggregated port. (if the port participates in the aggregation, this value is true.)

hwifMirrorPort.name: hwifMirrorPort
hwifMirrorPort.description: Whether it is a mirror port.

hwifVLANType.name: hwifVLANType
hwifVLANType.description: port vlan types. hybrid (3) port can carry multiple VLANs. If fabric function is supported, fabric(4) means the port is a fabric port.

hwifMcastControl.name: hwifMcastControl
hwifMcastControl.description: Broadcast storm suppression with the step length of 1, ranging from 1 to 100 percent. In some products the step is 5, ranging from 5 to 100.

hwifSrcMacControl.name: hwifSrcMacControl
hwifSrcMacControl.description: Whether to filter by source MAC address.

hwifClearStat.name: hwifClearStat
hwifClearStat.description: Clear all port statistics. Read operation not supported.

hwifXXBasePortIndex.name: hwifXXBasePortIndex
hwifXXBasePortIndex.description: Index number of the port and the first port index of the device is 1.

hwifPpsMcastControl.name: hwifPpsMcastControl
hwifPpsMcastControl.description: The broadcast suppression with pps(packet per second) type. The max value is determined by the port type and product.

hwifPpsBcastDisValControl.name: hwifPpsBcastDisValControl
hwifPpsBcastDisValControl.description: Control the port's pps(packet per second) broadcast suppression. When the port is enabled, its pps broadcast suppression value is the global disperse value, and when disabled, it doesn't suppress broadcast.

hwifUniSuppressionStep.name: hwifUniSuppressionStep
hwifUniSuppressionStep.description: The step of unicast suppression in ratio mode.

hwifPpsUniSuppressionMax.name: hwifPpsUniSuppressionMax
hwifPpsUniSuppressionMax.description: The max pps(packet per second) value of unicast suppression in pps mode.

hwifMulSuppressionStep.name: hwifMulSuppressionStep
hwifMulSuppressionStep.description: The step of multicast suppression in ratio mode.

hwifPpsMulSuppressionMax.name: hwifPpsMulSuppressionMax
hwifPpsMulSuppressionMax.description: The max pps(packet per second) value of multicast suppression in pps mode.

hwifUniSuppression.name: hwifUniSuppression
hwifUniSuppression.description: The unicast suppression with the ranging from 1 to 100 percent in ratio mode. The step is determined by hwifUniSuppressionStep.

hwifPpsUniSuppression.name: hwifPpsUniSuppression
hwifPpsUniSuppression.description: The unicast suppression in pps(packet per second) mode. The max value is determined by hwifPpsUniSuppressionMax.

hwifMulSuppression.name: hwifMulSuppression
hwifMulSuppression.description: The multicast suppression with ranging from 1 to 100 percent in ratio mode. The step is determined by hwifMulSuppressionStep.

hwifPpsMulSuppression.name: hwifPpsMulSuppression
hwifPpsMulSuppression.description: The multicast suppression in pps(packet per second) mode. The max pps value is determined by hwifPpsMulSuppressionMax.

hwifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax.name: hwifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax
hwifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the multicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Mbps) that a port can be configured.

hwifBMbpsMulSuppression.name: hwifBMbpsMulSuppression
hwifBMbpsMulSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based multicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Mbps. The upper limit of the multicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Mbps) is the value of hwifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax in the entry. The default value of hwifBMbpsMulSuppression is the value of hwifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax.

hwifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax.name: hwifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax
hwifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the multicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Kbps) that a port can be configured.

hwifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep.name: hwifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep
hwifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep.description: The step of multicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Kbps).

hwifBKbpsMulSuppression.name: hwifBKbpsMulSuppression
hwifBKbpsMulSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based multicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Kbps. The upper limit of the multicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Kbps) is the value of hwifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax in the entry. The value of hwifBKbpsMulSuppression must be multiple of the value of hwifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep. The default value of hwifBKbpsMulSuppression is the value of hwifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax.

hwifUnknownPacketDropMul.name: hwifUnknownPacketDropMul
hwifUnknownPacketDropMul.description: Control the port's unknown-multicast packets drop. When inbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-multicast packets in inbound direction. When outbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-multicast packets in outbound direction. When both directions are enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-multicast packets in both inbound and outbound directions.

hwifUnknownPacketDropUni.name: hwifUnknownPacketDropUni
hwifUnknownPacketDropUni.description: Control the port's unknown-unicast packets drop. When inbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-unicast packets in inbound direction. When outbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-unicast packets in outbound direction. When both directions are enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-unicast packets in both inbound and outbound directions.

hwifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax.name: hwifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax
hwifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the unicast suppression with bandwidth-based (Mbps) that a port can be configured.

hwifBMbpsUniSuppression.name: hwifBMbpsUniSuppression
hwifBMbpsUniSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based Unicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Mbps. The upper limit of the unicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Mbps) is the value of hwifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax in the entry. The default value of hwifBMbpsUniSuppression is the value of hwifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax.

hwifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax.name: hwifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax
hwifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the unicast suppression with bandwidth-based (Kbps) that a port can be configured.

hwifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep.name: hwifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep
hwifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep.description: The step of unicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Kbps).

hwifBKbpsUniSuppression.name: hwifBKbpsUniSuppression
hwifBKbpsUniSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based unicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Kbps. The upper limit of the unicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Kbps) is the value of hwifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax in the entry. The value of hwifBKbpsUniSuppression must be multiple of the value of hwifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep. The default value of hwifBKbpsUniSuppression is the value of hwifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax.

hwifOutPayloadOctets.name: hwifOutPayloadOctets
hwifOutPayloadOctets.description: The actual output octets of the interface.

hwifInPayloadOctets.name: hwifInPayloadOctets
hwifInPayloadOctets.description: The actual input octets of the interface.

hwifInErrorPktsRate.name: hwifInErrorPktsRate
hwifInErrorPktsRate.description: The rate of inbound error packets on the interface.

hwifInPkts.name: hwifInPkts
hwifInPkts.description: The number of packets received on the interface.

hwifInNormalPkts.name: hwifInNormalPkts
hwifInNormalPkts.description: The number of normal packets received on the interface.

hwifOutPkts.name: hwifOutPkts
hwifOutPkts.description: The number of packets sent on the interface.

hwifAggregatePortIndex.name: hwifAggregatePortIndex
hwifAggregatePortIndex.description: Index number of the main aggregated port.

hwifAggregateModel.name: hwifAggregateModel
hwifAggregateModel.description: Load sharing mode for the port aggregation.

hwifAggregateOperStatus.name: hwifAggregateOperStatus
hwifAggregateOperStatus.description: Current operation status of the row.

hwifHybridTaggedVlanListLow.name: hwifHybridTaggedVlanListLow
hwifHybridTaggedVlanListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each tagged VLAN of the hybrid port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is tagged in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not tagged if its bit has a value of '0'.

hwifHybridTaggedVlanListHigh.name: hwifHybridTaggedVlanListHigh
hwifHybridTaggedVlanListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each tagged VLAN of the hybrid port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is tagged in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not tagged if its bit has a value of '0'.

hwifHybridUnTaggedVlanListLow.name: hwifHybridUnTaggedVlanListLow
hwifHybridUnTaggedVlanListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each untagged VLAN of the hybrid port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is untagged in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not untagged if its bit has a value of '0'.

hwifHybridUnTaggedVlanListHigh.name: hwifHybridUnTaggedVlanListHigh
hwifHybridUnTaggedVlanListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each untagged VLAN of the hybrid port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is untagged in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not untagged if its bit has a value of '0'.

hwifComboPortIndex.name: hwifComboPortIndex
hwifComboPortIndex.description: The combo-port interface index. Its value is the same as the value of ifIndex in ifTable, but only includes indexes of the combo-port interfaces.

hwifComboPortCurActive.name: hwifComboPortCurActive
hwifComboPortCurActive.description: Current active interface of combo interfaces. The value 'fiber' means the interface with fiber connector of the pair of combo-port interfaces is active. The value 'copper' means the interface with copper connector of the pair is active. The value 'na' means not supported.

hwSwitchPortMax.name: hwSwitchPortMax
hwSwitchPortMax.description: Max ports that this switch includes.

hwifVLANTrunkStatusTable.name: hwifVLANTrunkStatusTable
hwifVLANTrunkStatusTable.description: Gvrp attributes on the VlanTrunk port.

hwifVLANTrunkStatusEntry.name: hwifVLANTrunkStatusEntry
hwifVLANTrunkStatusEntry.description: Gvrp attributes on the VlanTrunk port.

hwifVLANTrunkIndex.name: hwifVLANTrunkIndex
hwifVLANTrunkIndex.description: Index number of the VLANTrunk interface.

hwifVLANTrunkGvrpRegistration.name: hwifVLANTrunkGvrpRegistration
hwifVLANTrunkGvrpRegistration.description: GVRP registration information normal: This is the default configuration. Allow create, register and unregister vlans dynamiclly at this port. fixed: Aallow create and register vlan manually at this port. Prevent from unregistering vlans or registering known vlans of this port at another trunk port. forbidden: Unregister all vlans but vlan 1, forbid to create or register any other vlans at this port.

hwifVLANTrunkPassListLow.name: hwifVLANTrunkPassListLow
hwifVLANTrunkPassListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each actually passed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is actually passed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not actually passed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hwifVLANTrunkPassListHigh.name: hwifVLANTrunkPassListHigh
hwifVLANTrunkPassListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each actually passed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is actually passed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not actually passed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hwifVLANTrunkAllowListLow.name: hwifVLANTrunkAllowListLow
hwifVLANTrunkAllowListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each allowed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is allowed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not allowed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hwifVLANTrunkAllowListHigh.name: hwifVLANTrunkAllowListHigh
hwifVLANTrunkAllowListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each allowed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is allowed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not allowed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hwethernetEntry.name: hwethernetEntry
hwethernetEntry.description: Entries of Ethernet port attribute table

hwifEthernetMdi.name: hwifEthernetMdi
hwifEthernetMdi.description: Type of the line connected to the port. MDI-II (straight-through cable): 1 MDI-X (crossover cable): 2 MDI-AUTO (auto-sensing): 3

hwMaxMacLearn.name: hwMaxMacLearn
hwMaxMacLearn.description: The maximum number of MAC addresses that the port can learn. The value -1 means that the number of Mac addresses that the port can learn is unlimited.

hwifMacAddressLearn.name: hwifMacAddressLearn
hwifMacAddressLearn.description: This object indicates if the interface is allowed to learn mac address. eanbled(1) means the interface can learn mac address, otherwise disabled(2) can be set.

hwifEthernetTest.name: hwifEthernetTest
hwifEthernetTest.description: Test this interface. The actual testing will be different according to products. Read operation not supported.

hwifMacAddrLearnMode.name: hwifMacAddrLearnMode
hwifMacAddrLearnMode.description: Status indicates mac address learn mode of the interface. IVL(1) means independent VLAN learning. SVL means shared VLAN learning.

hwifEthernetFlowInterval.name: hwifEthernetFlowInterval
hwifEthernetFlowInterval.description: Set flow interval of the ethernet. The NMS should set value to integer which is a multiple of 5.

hwifEthernetIsolate.name: hwifEthernetIsolate
hwifEthernetIsolate.description: Isolate group means that all ports in the same isolate group can not send and receive packets each other. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight isolate groups, with the first octet specifying isolate groups 1 through 8, the second octet specifying isolate groups 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the leftmost bit is the first bit. the first bit represents the lowest numbered isolate group, and the last bit represents the highest numbered isolate group. one port can belong to more than one isolate group. Thus, each isolate group is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1', then that isolate group includes this port; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. for example, the first octet is '10000100' means that the port is included in the isolate group 1 and isolate group 6.

hwifVlanVPNTPID.name: hwifVlanVPNTPID
hwifVlanVPNTPID.description: Port based Vlan VPN TPID(Tag Protocol Indentifier), default value is 0x8100. Please refer to hwVlanVPNTPIDMode to get more information.

hwifIsolateGroupID.name: hwifIsolateGroupID
hwifIsolateGroupID.description: Isolate group identifier. Value zero means this interface does not belong to any isolate group.

hwifisUplinkPort.name: hwifisUplinkPort
hwifisUplinkPort.description: Ethernet uplink status, default value is 2.

hwifEthernetAutoSpeedMask.name: hwifEthernetAutoSpeedMask
hwifEthernetAutoSpeedMask.description: This object specifies which kinds of speed mode can be negotiated. Each bit corresponds to a kind of speed mode. If the value of a bit is '1', it means the corresponding speed mode is negotiable on the port. Otherwise the negotiation for that kind of speed mode is not supported on this port. If there are several negotiable speed modes, all bits for them are '1'. For example, if the speed mode 's10M' and 's1000M' can be negotiable, the value of this object is 0xA0.

hwifEthernetAutoSpeed.name: hwifEthernetAutoSpeed
hwifEthernetAutoSpeed.description: This object indicates which kinds of speed mode are negotiable on this port. Only when a bit of hwifEthernetAutoSpeedMask is '1', the corresponding bit of this object can be set to '1', indicating the corresponding speed mode is negotiable. For example, if the value of hwifEthernetAutoSpeedMask is 0xA0, which indicates speed mode 's10M' and 's1000M' are negotiable, the possible value of this object should be one of the four values (0x00, 0x20, 0x80 and 0xA0). If the value of hwifEthernetSpeed is not 'auto', the value of this object is insignificant and should be ignored. The value length of this object should be as long as that of hwifEthernetAutoSpeedMask.

hwIsolateGroupMax.name: hwIsolateGroupMax
hwIsolateGroupMax.description: Max isolate group that this device support, the value is zero means that the device does not support isolate group.

hwGlobalBroadcastMaxPps.name: hwGlobalBroadcastMaxPps
hwGlobalBroadcastMaxPps.description: The global max packets per second. When it is set, the value of BroadcastMaxPps in all ports will be changed to that setting.

hwGlobalBroadcastMaxRatio.name: hwGlobalBroadcastMaxRatio
hwGlobalBroadcastMaxRatio.description: The global max-ratio of broadcast from 0 to 100 percent. When it is set, the value of BroadcastMaxRatio in all ports will be changed to that setting.

hwVlanVPNTPIDMode.name: hwVlanVPNTPIDMode
hwVlanVPNTPIDMode.description: Vlan VPN TPID mode. The value 'port-based' means VLAN VPN TPID value would be set based on port via hwifVlanVPNTPID. In this situation, hwVlanVPNTPID is meaningless and always return 0x8100. The value 'global' means VLAN VPN TPID value should be set globally via hwVlanVPNTPID. In this situation, hwifVlanVPNTPID in hwethernetTable has the same value with hwVlanVPNTPID.

hwVlanVPNTPID.name: hwVlanVPNTPID
hwVlanVPNTPID.description: Global Vlan VPN TPID(Tag Protocol Indentifier), default value is 0x8100.

hwPortIsolateGroupIndex.name: hwPortIsolateGroupIndex
hwPortIsolateGroupIndex.description: Port isolate group identifier. The index of the hwPortIsolateGroupTable. The value ranges from 1 to the limit of isolate group quantity.

hwPortIsolateUplinkIfIndex.name: hwPortIsolateUplinkIfIndex
hwPortIsolateUplinkIfIndex.description: Index number of the uplink interface.

hwPortIsolateGroupRowStatus.name: hwPortIsolateGroupRowStatus
hwPortIsolateGroupRowStatus.description: Current operation status of the row.

hwPortIsolateGroupDescription.name: hwPortIsolateGroupDescription
hwPortIsolateGroupDescription.description: Port isolate group description, default value is zero-length string.

hwMaxMacLearnRange.name: hwMaxMacLearnRange
hwMaxMacLearnRange.description: The maximum number of MAC address that the port supports.
